examples: The dinner and the soiree too were done,
The supper too discuss’d, the dames admired,
The banqueteers had dropp’d off one by one—
The song was silent, and the dance expired:

verbs.description: banqueteer (third-person singular simple present banqueteers, present participle banqueteering, simple past and past participle banqueteered)

entries.meaning: To attend a banquet or banquets (particularly as a frequent or habitual activity).
examples: I had been banqueteering and making speeches two or three times in every week for six months  […]
